This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories, as it uses Push GP to automatically design optimisers for continuous-valued problems. It may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category, as the optimisers are population-based and could be used for control applications. Finally, it could belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category, as the paper discusses novel optimisation strategies that are not found within conventional optimisers.
